        {
            "title": "FLINT Corp announces significant debt reduction and capital structure simplification through recapitalization with key shareholder.",
            "id": "c55c27e7-563a-4c66-bebb-9d576f7b2260",
            "description": "FLINT Corp. (TSX: FLNT) in Calgary, Alberta, announced on Aug. 7, 2025, a proposed recapitalization transaction aimed at reducing the Company's debt and annual interest costs significantly. The plan also seeks to simplify the capital structure and enhance liquidity. This decision follows a thorough review process by the Company's Board, leading to the signing of a definitive recapitalization support agreement with Canso Investment Counsel Ltd., FLINT's largest shareholder and primary lender. The Recapitalization agreement, intended to benefit FLINT's shareholders and pave the way for future growth opportunities, will involve a significant reduction in debt load and interest costs, streamlining of the capital structure, and an improvement in liquidity.",
